      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Looks a good race for local galloper WARNA (6). In the placings at both runs this prep, most recently a closing third over 1400m at Sunshine Coast Poly. Overdue and gets chance. KEEP SAFE (9) missed the placings two runs back then didn't feature last start when 4.5 lengths away in ninth over 1200m at this track. That run was well off best figures but looks well placed here and gets chance to atone. NEPRAVDA (5) has missed the frame at both runs for new yard but not too far from the winner. Extra trip a plus and fitter again. Much better than last run and certainly worth another chance. ORIENTE (1) is ready to win and will take running down. TRIBBIANI (2) handles the ground and in the mix on best form.",
